Changes:
 granian (1.0.7) noble; urgency=medium
 .
   * Add per-application user= and group= support with root supervisor
     privilege dropping for Granian child processes.
   * Use granian:granian as the default child identity, use the user's
     primary group when only user= is set, and reject group= without user=.
   * Move default logs to /var/log/granian/<app>/<app>.log and prepare
     per-app log and runtime directories with the target owner and mode.
   * Re-apply per-app log/runtime directory ownership and mode at start.
   * Make normal Granian options last-wins while keeping documented
     repeatable options append-only.
   * Add venv fail-fast validation, granian-bin override, and
     --dry-run/--print-command diagnostics.
   * Restrict explicit log-file and error-log-file paths to /var/log/granian.
   * Harden log and directory handling against symlinks and non-regular
     log files.
   * Return a failing supervisor status when apps are disabled after repeated
     failures.
   * Update logrotate for new and legacy log paths with a 20M size limit.
   * Prevent automatic systemd service enable/start/restart during package
     installation and upgrades.
   * Update systemd units, default configuration, example configuration,
     and README documentation for the new privilege and logging model.
